                            <comment id="12558448" author="bryanduxbury" created="Sun, 13 Jan 2008 20:59:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch just contains a unit test that is intended to fail. Only need to &quot;submit&quot; a patch once it&apos;s ready to be tested for committing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12591390" author="clint.morgan" created="Tue, 22 Apr 2008 18:09:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This bug seems to have gone away in the last month.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13042700" author="subbaswathi" created="Thu, 2 Jun 2011 10:53:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this is same in hbase 0.90.3 version also...even if we delete that colum family member ie column Qualifier using deletecolumn API,that is still present..(If we do the scan ,we can able to see that columnfamily member)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13042858" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 2 Jun 2011 16:40:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;deleteColumn only deletes the latest version eg if you have an older version it will become the new most recent Put. Try using deleteColumns, and please read the javadoc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13043221" author="subbaswathi" created="Fri, 3 Jun 2011 05:49:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;even if i use deleteColumns and deleteFamily API,i am able to get that family if i do scan..&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13043868" author="jdcryans" created="Fri, 3 Jun 2011 16:58:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you demonstrate that with a unit test? Take a look at how we do it with TestFromClientSide.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13044772" author="ram_krish" created="Mon, 6 Jun 2011 10:16:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;thank you..its working fine...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13045287" author="subbaswathi" created="Tue, 7 Jun 2011 06:10:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;its working fine...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13047462" author="jdcryans" created="Fri, 10 Jun 2011 21:19:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So what was the issue then?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13048294" author="subbaswathi" created="Sun, 12 Jun 2011 11:14:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;if we delete the column using admin.deletecolumn API,we need not use this table.delete(delete) again...but if we delete the column using delete.deletecolumn API ,then we should use table.delete(delete)(here table is a htable object)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
